==English==
===Etymology===
From early modern French ''[[fascher]]'' (now ''[[fâcher]]''), from Latin ''[[fastus]]'' ‘disdain’.

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/fæʃ/}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-æʃ|-æʃ]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|fashes|'''[[fashing]]''' ''or'' '''[[fashin]]'''|fashed|fashed}}

# {{italbrac|Scotland & Northern UK}} To [[worry]]; to [[bother]], [[annoy]].
#: ''"Divint '''fash''' yersel"'' = "don't worry"

===Noun===
{{en-noun|fashes}}

# {{italbrac|Scotland & Northern UK}} A [[worry]]; [[trouble]]; [[bother]].

